  "doc_id": "33912",
  "text": "Overall, the estimated global carbon cycle temperature sensitivities presented here are substantially lower than best estimates for carbon-cycle climate sensitivities quantified for multi-decadal to centennial time-scales during the preindustrial past millennium [CITATION_1] . Our comparison among forcing scenarios clearly demonstrates how even small biases in absolute temperature and/or precipitation in coupled carbon-cycle climate simulations can contribute to a wide spread and possible overestimation of the strength of carbon cycle feedbacks . Compared to the sensitivity of the inferred terrestrial carbon sink, it thus appears particularly important to have unbiased estimates of climate when trying to diagnose vegetation coupling in earth system simulations.",
